1 Add pathology from Ingmar review

ingmar_db <- read_xlsx("./data/ingmar-review.xlsx") %>% clean_names()

# Prepend "ingmar_" to all column names except "mrn"
ingmar_db <- ingmar_db %>%
  rename_with(~ if_else(. == "mrn", ., paste0("ingmar_", .)), everything())

mrf_select <- left_join(mrf_select, ingmar_db, by="mrn")

mrf_select <- mrf_select %>% mutate(path_new = ifelse(is.na(ingmar_pathology), path, ingmar_pathology))
mrf_select <- mrf_select %>% filter(complete.cases(mrf_narrative_summary))
nrow(mrf_select)

4 How many cases? Proportion where MRF is useful?

#describe(mrf_raw$mrf_finding_code)

ggplot(mrf_select, aes(x = mrf_finding_code, fill = mrf_finding_code)) +
  geom_bar(aes(y = (after_stat(count)/sum(after_stat(count))))) +
  geom_text(aes(y = (after_stat(count))/sum(after_stat(count)),
                label = scales::percent((after_stat(count)) / sum(after_stat(count)))),
            stat = "count", vjust = 1.5,
            color = "white", size = 5) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) +
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(y = "Percentage", title = "How does MRF compare to clinical imaging?", subtitle = paste("N=", nrow(mrf_select), "patients")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = get_pal("oriole"))

5 What types of additional findings are seen by MRF?

ggplot(additional_findings, aes(x=mrf_narrative_summary, fill=mrf_narrative_summary)) + 
  geom_bar() + stat_count(binwidth = 1, 
             geom = 'text', 
             color = 'white', 
             aes(label = after_stat(count)),
           position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) + 
   labs(x = NULL, title = "What is MRF adding?", subtitle = paste("MRF additional finding subgroup, N=", nrow(additional_findings), "patients")) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = get_pal("oriole"))

6 Which types of pathology are BEST picked up by MRF?

Filtered data for those who have pathology available

# choose end colours
seq_col <- get_pal("oriole")[c(2,7)]  

# create a gradient of 50 shades in between the selected colours 
long_col <- colorRampPalette(seq_col)(14)
ggplot(path_available, aes(x=path_new, fill=path_new, by = mrf_finding_code)) + 
  geom_bar() + stat_count(binwidth = 1, 
             geom = 'text', 
             color = 'white', 
             aes(label = after_stat(count)),
           position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
   labs(x = NULL, title = "Which pathology is seen? Grouped by MRF finding", subtitle = paste("Patients with pathology available, N=", nrow(path_available), "patients")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = long_col) +
  facet_wrap(~ mrf_finding_code, nrow = 1)
